  "prompt": "In which attempt is NET/SET exam cleared approximately?",
  "response": "The NET (National Eligibility Test) and SET (State Eligibility Test) exams are competitive and challenging, and the number of attempts required to clear them can vary widely among individuals based on factors such as preparation, background knowledge, study habits, and exam-taking strategies.\n\nOn average, many candidates may clear the NET/SET exam within 1 to 3 attempts. Some may succeed on their first try, while others may need several attempts to achieve the required qualifying marks. \n\nSuccess in these exams often depends on consistent and focused preparation, understanding the exam pattern, practicing previous years' papers, and staying updated with the syllabus and relevant study materials. It is essential to have a well-organized study plan and possibly seek guidance from mentors or coaching institutes if needed.",
